Used to/would

We use used to + verb to talk about regular past actions that do not happen now. 

I used to take the bus to work every day. 
(But now I take the train.)

We also used to + verb when we talk about past situations that are no longer true.

He used to be a soilder. 
(But now he's a teacher.)

We can also use would + verb to talk about regular past actions that do not happen now.

When we first moved here, people would stop and talk in the street. They don't now.

Would is use for past actions, not situations.

France used to have a king. 
*** NOT France would have a king. ***
